linkedlist

Class LinkedList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • linkedlist.LinkedList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The element type this LinkedList is going to contain.

    public class LinkedList<E>
extends java.lang.Object
    This implementation of a singly linked LinkedList provides insertion time at first O(1) and deletion time at first O(1), at cost of search, insertion and deletion anywhere with cost O(n).

      • add

        public void add(int index,
                E element)
        Adds an element element to the LinkedList at index idx.
        Parameters:
        index - The index where the element is going to be added. Take care, the index can't be bigger than the size of the LinkedList, but it could be equal, then is like appending to the LinkedList.
        element - The element to be added.

      • remove

        public void remove(int index)
        Removes the element in the LinkedList at index idx.
        Parameters:
        index - The index of the element to be removed. Index cant be equal to the LinkedList's size: remember 0-indexing.
